extends ../layouts/application.jade

block content
  h1.sr-only Introduction to Javascript: Loops, Array and Objects
  div.page-header
    h2 Class #2: The Fundamentals

  p.lead
    | Building upon the concepts covered in 
    a(href='/classes/one') Class #1
    | , here we discuss arrays and objects and the process &amp; usefulness of iterating over them to do stuff programmatically.

  p
    a.btn.btn-info(href='/slides/two')
      i.fa.fa-picture-o
      |  &nbsp;View Slides
    | &nbsp;&nbsp;
    a.btn.btn-warning.disabled
      i.fa.fa-codepen
      |  &nbsp;View Codepen

  // -
    div.page-header
      h2 Class Overview

    p Let's imagine- you have a array of things you want to display on a webpage. Each thing is similar but also has it's own individual attributes, like color and name. This week we'll learn how to take a group of objects like this and print their attributes on the page.
    br
    ol
      li Review
      li Loops
      li Arrays
      li Objects

    div.page-header
      h2 Quiz

    div.well
      div.question
        h4 1). What is a variable?
        div.radio
          each opt, i in ['A new Saison from Rhinegeist.','Container that holds a value.','A star whose brightness as seen from Earth is fluctuating.','None of the above.']
            label
              input(type='radio',name='1',value=(i+1))
              = opt
            br

      hr
      div.question
        h4 2). How can you tell that a variable is a string?
        div.radio
          each opt, i in ['It has words.', 'It isnâ€™t a number.', 'It has a semicolon.', 'It has single or double quotes.']
            label
              input(type='radio',name='2',value=(i+1))
              = opt
            br

      hr
      div.question
        h4 3). What is a function?
        div.radio
          each opt, i in ['Container that holds a value.', 'Block of code designed to perform a particular task.', 'Relationship or expression involving one or more variables.', 'Part of the chorus to a song by School House Rock.']
            label
              input(type='radio',name='3',value=(i+1))
              = opt
            br

      hr
      div.question
        h4 4). Why would you use a function?
        div.radio
          each opt, i in ['Reuse code more than once.', 'Different arguments produce different results.', 'Keep your code organized.', 'All of the above.']
            label
              input(type='radio',name='4',value=(i+1))
              = opt
            br

      hr
      div.question
        h4 5). What element links a JS file to an HTML file?
        div.radio
          each opt, i in ['<head>', '<javascript>', '<script>', '<img>']
            label
              input(type='radio',name='5',value=(i+1))
              code= opt
            br

      hr
      div.question
        h4 6). What's the difference between = and ==?
        div.radio
          each opt, i in ['Assignment vs. comparison.', 'Short vs. Long.', 'Stylistic preference.', 'SYKE! There is no difference.']
            label
              input(type='radio',name='6',value=(i+1))
              = opt
            br

      hr
      div.question
        h4 7). How do you negate a statement?
        div.radio
          each opt, i in ['Execute it twice in a row.', 'Use two semicolons.', 'Put it in a function called negate()', 'Use the exclamation-point (!) operator']
            label
              input(type='radio',name='7',value=(i+1))
              = opt
            br

      hr
      div.question
        h4 8). What is a data-type?
        div.radio
          each opt, i in ['Container that holds a value.', 'Defines the values that a variable can hold.', 'Defines the arguments a function can take.', 'None of the above.']
            label
              input(type='radio',name='8',value=(i+1))
              = opt
            br

      hr
      div.question
        h4 9). How many days did it take to write Javascript?
        div.radio
          each opt, i in ['100 days', '1 week', '10 days', '3 months']
            label
              input(type='radio',name='9',value=(i+1))
              = opt
            br

      hr
      div.question
        h4 10). Which data-type is used to store a collection of things?
        div.radio
          each opt, i in ['Variable', 'String', 'Function', 'Array']
            label
              input(type='radio',name='10',value=(i+1))
              = opt
            br


